  "text": "The key host organism difference might be in immune response to thyroid cancer (Boyd & Baker 1996 [CITATION_1] . A variety of observations support the importance of that response in preventing PTC metastasis or recurrence in adults [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] and children [CITATION_5] . Gupta found that the pediatric PTC patients with the greatest number of proliferating lymphocytes in thyroid infiltrates had the longest disease-free survival. Of interest, intense tumor expression of the B7-2 antigen has been correlated with a greater propensity for recurrence in children and adolescents with DTC [CITATION_6] .",
